China's state environmental protection administration ( ) said here on wednesday that the songhua river in northeast china suffered a major water pollution incident owing to the explosion of a petrochemical plant at the upper reaches.
"we will be very clear about who's responsible," zhang lijun the state environmental protection administration, said at a press conference.
The fengman hydropower station in the upper reach of songhua river increased the daily discharge amount from 600 cubic meters per second to 1,000 cubic meters per second starting from 10:00 a.m. .
